CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 13, 1972, pg. 2, reads: "LISTEN TO COMPLAINTS - Governor Milton Shapp, seated, center, the Rev. Jesse Jackson of PUSH, seated, left, and Roland Hayes, seated right, listen to grievances by some citizens during a visit to the Hill District last week. Standing, left side of room, left to right, Harvey Adams, presidents The Guardians, Nate Smith, Chairman Black Solidarity Fair Committee, John Brweer [Brewer] and William Gree, School Board officials, listen."
TitMainTitle: Copy of a photograph of Harvey Adams, C. Delores Tucker, Jesse Jackson, Governor Milton Shapp, Roland Hayes gathered around table, and Nate Smith, Bill Fisher, and John Brewer, Sr., standing behind them, for press conference
